        <h1 style="white-space: nowrap;">Spot the International Space Station</h1>
        <p>
            The ISS is the largest human constructed satellite, and is in a near Earth orbit at about 400 kilometers above sea level.
            This makes it the third brightest object in the sky! It can be easily spotted from the ground if you know when and where to look.
        </p>
        <p>
            Although the station can be very bright, it is traveling at an average speed of 7.67 km/sec (17,200 mph), and is only visible for a few minutes at a time.
            The tool to the right, provided by NASA, shows the next opportunity to spot the station. If you are outside of Corvallis, visit 
            <a href="https://spotthestation.nasa.gov/">NASA's spot the station website</a> for siting opportunities all around the world.
        </p>
       
